cs.MS, cs.NA, cs.DC, cs.CE, cs.SC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is likely because the paper presents a generic algorithm for numbering and iterating over data values in finite element simulations. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is likely because the paper evaluates the performance of the algorithm on a range of low compute intensity operations in finite element simulations. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is possible because the paper discusses the performance of the algorithm on different hardware architectures. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is possible because the paper discusses the application of extruded meshes in geophysical finite element simulations. 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is unlikely because the paper does not involve symbolic computation.
